<p><strong>There can be different ways to get the job done.</strong></p>

<p>Variables given:
 1. start=6 
 2. stop=10</p>

<h3>You can try this also, for different approach:</h3>

<pre><code>def mirror_numbers(start,stop):
  if start&lt;stop:
    val=range(start,stop)
    return [j if i &lt; len(val) else -j for i,j in enumerate([x for x in val]*2) ]

mirror_numbers(6,10)
</code></pre>
